# L4-oracle.locke -- Contract for the hardened L4 oracle layer.
#
# This Locke specifies the invariants that @site/src/oracle.py must
# satisfy.  L4 is invoked by L3 (engine) through the oracle_backend
# callback and provides: OracleBackend protocol, backend registry,
# tool sandbox, fuel-bounded agentic kernel, LLM wrapper, usage
# tracking, and concrete backends (LiteLLM, Claude Code).

## Identity

name:    L4-oracle
layer:   L4
source:  @site/src/oracle.py
tests:   @site/tests/L4-oracle/
depends: (none -- invoked by L3 through oracle_backend callback)

## Dependency constraint

oracle.py imports ONLY Python stdlib (hashlib, inspect, json, os, signal,
pathlib, typing) + litellm (lazy, optional) + claude_code_sdk (lazy,
optional).  No imports from kernel.py, forms.py, seal.py, or engine.py.
No husks.utils.trace coupling.  No module-level mutable state except
the backend and tool registries.

## Types

RealizedCost(TypedDict): tokens_in, tokens_out, cost_usd, fuel_steps
  Provenance only.  None enter the Merkle DAG.

OracleBackend(Protocol): name: str, run(S, rule_name, recipe, outputs, config) -> RealizedCost
  Must: (1) confine effects to site + readonly roots, (2) permit only
  recipe tools, (3) stop at recipe fuel, (4) raise on non-clean exit,
  (5) return RealizedCost.  Must NOT read config from recipe.

## Backend registry

register(backend) -> None: register under backend.name, idempotent
get_backend(name) -> OracleBackend: lazy-loads litellm/claude-code on first use
  Unknown name -> KeyError

## Shared scaffolding

DEFAULT_TOOLS = ["read-file", "write-file", "list-dir", "tree"]
build_system_prompt(site, outputs) -> str: oracle standing orders
site_of(S) -> Path: resolve stage or site
readonly_roots_of(S) -> set[Path]: resolve readonly-dirs

## Tool sandbox

MAX_WRITE_SIZE = 10 MB
MAX_TOOL_TIMEOUT = 30 seconds

sandbox(path, write=, site_root=, readonly_roots=) -> Path
  Resolves path within sandbox.  Raises ValueError on escape.
  write=True: site_root only (never readonly_roots).
  site_root=None: no confinement.

## Tool registry

@tool decorator: registers fn, auto-generates OpenAI function schema
schemas(names=) -> list: OpenAI tool definitions, filtered by names
dispatch(name, args, context=, timeout=) -> str
  Calls tool with SIGALRM timeout.  Returns error string on any exception.

## Built-in tools

read_file(path) -> str: file contents, error on escape/missing/binary/dir
write_file(path, content) -> "ok": creates parents, rejects oversized/escape
list_dir(path) -> str: sorted names, one level
tree(path, depth=3) -> str: recursive listing, skips hidden/__pycache__/escapes

All tools accept site_root/readonly_roots kwargs for explicit sandboxing.

## Usage tracker

UsageTracker: cumulative token/cost tracker, one per build
  track(response, rule=): accumulate from litellm response
  snapshot() -> dict: calls, tokens, cost, by_rule, model
  No module-level default tracker.

## LLM wrapper (lazy litellm)

DEFAULT_MODEL = "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001"
_litellm(): lazy import, raises ModuleNotFoundError with install hint

llm_call(prompt, model=, max_tokens=, system=, tools=, temperature=,
         tracker=, params=, router=) -> response
llm_call_messages(messages, model=, ...) -> response
llm_meta(response) -> dict: model, tokens, finish_reason, cost, text

## Provenance hashing

compute_config_hash(model, max_tokens, temperature=, tools=) -> hex64
compute_prompt_hash(prompt) -> hex64
  Deterministic SHA-256.  For provenance, never enters seal.

## Kernel: response parsing

MAX_TOOL_OUTPUT = 8000
parse_response(r) -> dict: type in {act, acts, stop, say}
  act: single tool call (tool, args, tool_call_id)
  acts: parallel tool calls (list of call dicts)
  stop: model finished (value)
  say: text without tool call or stop

## Kernel: message building

_build_messages(C) -> list: OpenAI messages from prompt + trace
  Reconstructs assistant+tool message pairs from trace events.
  Supports act (single) and acts (parallel) trace entries.

## Kernel: context helpers

_rebind(C, event) -> C': immutable append to trace
_allowed(C, tool_name) -> bool: check allowlist
_dispatch_context(C) -> dict: extract site_root/readonly_roots for dispatch

## Kernel: agentic loop

invoke_llm(C) -> dict: call LLM, return parsed response
step(M, C, fuel) -> dict: iterative loop until stop/halt/error/kill
  act: check allowlist, dispatch, rebind, burn fuel
  acts: per-call allowlist+dispatch+fuel, partial halt if exhausted mid-batch
  say: return immediately
  stop: return immediately
  fuel=0: halt
agent(C, fuel=8, M=None) -> dict: setup tool-defs, delegate to step

## Config resolution

_resolve_config(config, rule_name) -> dict
  Merges per-rule override over base config.
  One-level deep merge: if both base and override have a dict value for
  the same key (e.g. params), the dicts are merged instead of replaced.
  Scalar overrides still replace.

## LiteLLMBackend

name = "litellm"
run(S, rule_name, recipe, outputs, config):
  1. Resolve config (per_rule override with deep merge)
  2. Create UsageTracker, build system prompt
  3. Call agent() with prompt/tools/system/model/params/router/site_root/readonly_roots
  4. _raise_unless_stop(result)
  5. Return RealizedCost from tracker snapshot

## ClaudeCodeBackend

name = "claude-code"
CC_TOOL_MAP: husk tool -> Claude Code tool mapping
_Gate: per-invocation interceptor (allowlist + fuel + sandbox)
  decide(tool_name, tool_input) -> (allow, reason)
  Checks: allowed set, path confinement, fuel counter

run(S, rule_name, recipe, outputs, config):
  1. Map husk tools to CC tools (unmapped -> RuntimeError)
  2. Create _Gate
  3. Remove CLAUDECODE env var (prevents nested session detection)
  4. asyncio.run(_run_async(...))
  5. Check gate.exhausted -> RuntimeError
  6. Return RealizedCost

_run_async: lazy import claude_code_sdk, query() with can_use_tool interceptor

## Dispatcher

run_oracle(S, rule_name, recipe, outputs) -> RealizedCost
  Selects backend from S["oracle-backend-name"] (default "litellm").
  Config from S["oracle-config"].
  Per-rule backend: resolves config for the rule first; if the resolved
  config contains a "backend" key, that backend is used instead of the
  global one.

## Backend-blind sealing invariant

Backend selection and config live in S, never in the recipe.
Recipe form: (oracle name prompt tools fuel).  No model, provider,
sampling params, router, or backend name.  Changing backend/config
does NOT re-fire sealed rules.

## What is NOT in L4

- Node constructors, build evaluator, cache -- L3-engine
- Seal I/O, path sandboxing for build -- L2-seal
- CSE codec, content hashing -- L0-kernel
- Form bijection -- L1-forms
- husks.utils.trace coupling -- removed (events in kernel context)

## Verification command

    python -m pytest @site/tests/L4-oracle/ -v --tb=short
